Business Brief -- Alexander's Inc.:
   Trump Partnership Enters
   Into Citibank Loan Accord
The amended agreement was reached in connection with a
debt restructuring of Trump and some of its affiliates. As
previously reported, Donald J. Trump has agreed to give his
lenders a 49% ownership share in the Plaza Hotel in exchange
for more favorable terms on the property's more than $600
million in debt.
   According to the SEC filing, Trump-Alexander currently
intends to transfer the shares to the bank on June 30, 1995,
or earlier in the event that the bank makes a demand for
payment of the new note.
   Trump-Alexander is a New York general partnership. At last
report, Mr. Trump held about 27% of Alexander's shares
outstanding. The company has about 4,970,000 shares
outstanding.